--------------------
**Leaked statements.** Leaked audited financial documents, independently [v=
erified](https://arstechnica.com/ai/2026/06/leaked-financial-docs-show-open=
ai-is-losing-billions-of-dollars-a-year/) by the Financial Times, show Open=
AI posted a $38.5 billion net loss in 2025 =E2=80=94 over 7X the $5 billion=
 loss it posted in 2024. Revenue grew as well, from $3.7B to $13B, but not =
fast enough to outpace its losses.

**Awkward timing.** The same day, a separate report found that ChatGPT=E2=
=80=99s market share has [dipped below](https://techcrunch.com/2026/06/16/c=
hatgpts-market-share-slips-below-50-for-first-time/) 50% for the first time=
 ever, thanks to rising competition from Google's Gemini, Anthropic's Claud=
e, and xAI's Grok. The news lands at an inopportune time: OpenAI filed [con=
fidentially](https://openai.com/index/openai-submits-confidential-s-1/) to =
go public just last week. But don=E2=80=99t count the AI leader out just ye=
t.

**The SpaceX precedent.** Investors have proved they=E2=80=99re willing to =
sweep less-than-ideal financials under the rug =E2=80=94 as long as the com=
pany=E2=80=99s ambitions are big enough. SpaceX=E2=80=99s IPO is proof of t=
hat. Its S-1 disclosed a $4.28 billion loss in Q1 2026 and roughly $41 bill=
ion in cumulative losses since founding, yet it still landed the largest IP=
O on record.

**The question.** Elon Musk was able to shift SpaceX=E2=80=99s IPO conversa=
tion from today=E2=80=99s financials to tomorrow=E2=80=99s potential. Despi=
te its cash burn, OpenAI still boasts one of the fastest-growing consumer p=
latforms of all time. Can Sam Altman craft a similarly successful storyline=
? Only time will tell.=20


